  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dba \u0d85\u0daf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Electricity bill debate today",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The debate regarding the government's decision to increase the electricity bill will be held in Parliament today (29) when the House is adjourned.",
        "The Parliament is scheduled to meet today (29) at 9:30 in the morning under the chairmanship of Speaker Mahinda Yapa Abeywardena.",
        "The proposal for the debate is presented by the People's Power Party.",
        "The speaker's office said that the debate will be held from 9:30 am to 4:30 pm.",
        "The government has already decided to increase the electricity bill by 70 percent. Various parties including political parties and mass organizations have already protested the government in this regard.",
        "Meanwhile, the second reading debate on the Budget Appropriation Bill is scheduled to be held tomorrow (30), tomorrow (31), next 1st and 2nd.",
        "President Ranil Wickramasinghe will present the budget proposals (budget speech) tomorrow (30) morning.",
        "After the President presents the budget speech, Parliament will be adjourned until the following day (31). Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena recently presented the Budget Appropriation (Amendment) Bill for the next four months to the Parliament."
      ],
